{"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"With the release of 0.26.0 comes a new migration flow for ATProtoKit developers. This change is fairly small, but this article will still cover what to expect in order to clear any confusion.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"text":"Authentication Flow","anchor":"Authentication-Flow","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Previously, when you wanted to authenticate to an AT Protocol service, you used an initializer from "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", which contained the "},{"code":"handle","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"password","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" parameters. Then, you would use ATProtocolConfiguration.authenticate(authenticationFactorToken:) and passed the instance to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoKit","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration(handle: example.bsky.social, password: hunter2)","","Task {","    do {","        \/\/ You can put it in here…","        try await config.authenticate()","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Or here…","        try await config.authenticate()","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With version 0.26, this has been changed slightly:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration()","","Task {","    do {","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Enter the handle and password in here.","        try await config.authenticate(","            handle: example.bsky.social,","            password: hunter2","        )","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here are the changes being made:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"text":"’s initializer no longer takes the ","type":"text"},{"code":"handle","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"password"},{"text":" parameters: now, ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)"},{"text":" is responsible.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the only external change. However, more has been made internally:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSession","isActive":true},{"text":" is no longer stored inside of ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference"},{"text":": now, a new ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":" named "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSessionRegistry","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" holds all instances of the "},{"code":"struct","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UUID"},{"text":" value has been added to the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". This value is linked to all objects that are related to the session. This is part of the new initializer for "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", named "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"text":" now closely follows ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SessionConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":". In fact, the following methods are no longer stored in the "},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", but have moved to default implementations of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","type":"reference"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/getSession()","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/refreshSession()"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/deleteSession()","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}]}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A new "},{"code":"protocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", named "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", will now manage the management of the password, access token, and refresh token. An "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":", named "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is available for applications running on Apple’s platforms."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"`SessionConfiguration`","anchor":"SessionConfiguration","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As mentioned previously, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SessionConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":" now has default configurations for each of the required methods. It is also "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sendable"},{"text":" and requires a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":" to conform to it. The default implementation assumes you’re using an App Password to authenticate by default, but you’re able to create new implementations for your own conforming "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Furthermore, the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)-272a8"},{"type":"text","text":" method handles Two-Factor Authentication, but the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"type":"text","text":" can also handle OAuth. This is thanks to a "},{"code":"AsyncStream","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"-related properties, named ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeContinuation"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeStream"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Auto-managing-the-Keychain","text":"Auto-managing the Keychain"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"As mentioned earlier, a new ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" have been made: "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" respectively. This manages the keychain items for the password and refresh token, as well as storing the access token in-memory.","type":"text"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The access token is being stored in-memory due to how frequently the token expires.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" conforms to ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","isActive":true},{"text":" and is the default object used for Apple platforms. It’s also the default object used when initializing with ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference"},{"text":". However, you’re free to create your own implementation if it doesn’t suit your needs.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"At this time, Linux and Windows developers will need to implement their own "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":" to achieve the same effect. However, default "},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"s for those platforms will be created at a later date."}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit"]]},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"ATProtoKit"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"0.21 to 0.26 Authentication Flow Migration"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/0210AuthFlowChange"},"kind":"article","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/atprotokit\/0210authflowchange"]}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn about how to set up your project with the new authentication flow changes."}],"references":{"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/SessionConfiguration/codeStream":{"url":"\/documentation\/atprotokit\/sessionconfiguration\/codestream","required":true,"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The async stream that receives user-provided authentication codes."}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","title":"codeStream","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"codeStream","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScS","text":"AsyncStream","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"String","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeStream"},"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/UserSession":{"abstract":[{"text":"Represents an authenticated user session within the AT Protocol.","type":"